1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,200
Month-end review often splits one decision
across a ledger, invoice,

2
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:06,300
policy, spreadsheet, and sign-off.

3
00:00:06,300 --> 00:00:11,100
BalanceDocket gives controllers one
evidence-bound path through the exception,

4
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:15,000
keeping calculation, model advice,
and human authority separate.

5
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:20,000
This is a bundled synthetic June close.
Through the BalanceDocket skill,

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:25,300
Codex generates the fixture, runs the
local case, checks status, and prepares

7
00:00:25,300 --> 00:00:30,700
the bounded advisory. The baseline needs
no model, network,

8
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:34,000
OpenAI account, or API key.

9
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,400
Inside Adjustments, the invoice period
runs from June fifteenth,

10
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:42,500
twenty twenty-six, through June
fourteenth, twenty twenty-seven.

11
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:47,100
Controls—not the model—verify its
identity and cutoff, then allocate

12
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:51,600
sixteen of three hundred sixty-five
days to June:

13
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:55,900
five thousand two hundred sixty kronor
and twenty-seven öre expense;

14
00:00:55,900 --> 00:01:00,100
one hundred fourteen thousand seven
hundred thirty-nine kronor

15
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:02,000
and seventy-three öre prepaid.

16
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:07,300
This retained Codex run requested
GPT-5.6 Sol

17
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:12,100
through my eligible ChatGPT plan,
without an API key.

18
00:01:12,100 --> 00:01:16,700
BalanceDocket sent bounded synthetic
excerpts, exact amounts,

19
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:21,300
and a strict schema. The result passed
schema, citation, amount,

20
00:01:21,300 --> 00:01:26,400
no-authority, and snapshot checks.

21
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:31,000
Codex CLI did not report the returned
model, so I disclose the request

22
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:36,000
without claiming independent confirmation.

23
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:39,600
The result is labeled
“Codex requested, validated output.”

24
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:43,900
It selected three source-linked citations,
reported medium uncertainty,

25
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:47,500
and flagged missing evidence.
Provider prose was discarded.

26
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:51,900
BalanceDocket builds the conclusion
locally from validated selections

27
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:56,300
and fixed amounts. The advisory cannot
change calculations, approve, post,

28
00:01:56,300 --> 00:02:00,000
lock, pay, file, send, or alter
source data.

29
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,100
Authority stays with the reviewer.

30
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:08,500
I record that the cited service period and
exact integer-öre allocation support

31
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:13,600
prepaid treatment, while missing
evidence needs follow-up.

32
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:17,900
I choose Request evidence—the safe,
repeatable disposition.

33
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:23,500
The decision stays bound to this snapshot
in an append-only local hash chain;

34
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:25,000
no ERP write occurs.

35
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:29,000
The workpaper binds source hashes,
deterministic calculation,

36
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:34,100
advisory hash, human rationale, action,
snapshot, chain head,

37
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:38,000
and validation scope. It reports
zero accounting actions

38
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:42,000
and zero ERP writes, so another reviewer
can audit the decision.

39
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,900
Codex accelerated the Python and React
build, tests,

40
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:48,400
accessibility, and release checks.

41
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:52,000
I made every product decision
and final judgment.
